<paragraph id="8BC236E57918FFB943429D29D55CFA4D" blockId="16.[491,1582,1398,1733]" pageId="16" pageNumber="280">
Remarks — This species was known only from its 
<typeStatus id="54C688477918FFB945169D28D357FA34" box="[1095,1141,1399,1423]" pageId="16" pageNumber="280">type</typeStatus>
series collected from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667918FFB944359D29D29BFA35" authorityName="F.Boie" authorityYear="1822" box="[1380,1465,1398,1422]" class="Aves" family="Ardeidae" genus="Ardeola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pelecaniformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="280" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B909EAF77918FFB944359D29D29BFA35" box="[1380,1465,1398,1422]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="280">Ardeola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B909EAF77918FFB940BA9DC6D56BFA0A" box="[491,585,1433,1457]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="280">ralloides</emphasis>
(Scopoli) (
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667918FFB943939DC6D44EFA0A" box="[706,876,1433,1457]" class="Aves" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pelecaniformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="280" phylum="Chordata" rank="order">Pelecaniformes</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667918FFB942299DC6D4D3FA0A" box="[888,1009,1433,1457]" class="Aves" family="Ardeidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pelecaniformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="280" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Ardeidae</taxonomicName>
) in 
<collectingCountry id="F36A76757918FFB9454C9DC6D38CFA0A" box="[1053,1198,1433,1457]" name="Mozambique" pageId="16" pageNumber="280">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
(near Limpopo River mouth). Here it is recorded outside the 
<typeStatus id="54C688477918FFB9420D9DE3D4A8FA6F" box="[860,906,1468,1492]" pageId="16" pageNumber="280">type</typeStatus>
locality, in 
<collectingCountry id="F36A76757918FFB945589DE3D3A0FA68" box="[1033,1154,1467,1491]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="16" pageNumber="280">DR Congo</collectingCountry>
and on 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667918FFB945FD9DE4D21FFA68" authorityName="Oberholser" authorityYear="1925" box="[1196,1341,1467,1491]" class="Aves" family="Jacanidae" genus="Actophilornis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Charadriiformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="280" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B909EAF77918FFB945FD9DE4D21FFA68" box="[1196,1341,1467,1491]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="280">Actophilornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667918FFB944159DE4D28AFA68" box="[1348,1448,1467,1491]" class="Aves" family="Jacanidae" genus="Actophilornis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Charadriiformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="280" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="africanus">
<emphasis id="B909EAF77918FFB944159DE4D28AFA68" box="[1348,1448,1467,1491]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="280">africanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the first time.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC236E57918FFB943429E5ED362F97E" blockId="16.[491,1582,1398,1733]" pageId="16" pageNumber="280">
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667918FFB943429E5ED5C8F9A2" authorityName="Vercammen-Grandjean" authorityYear="1960" box="[531,746,1537,1561]" class="Arachnida" family="Trombiculidae" genus="Blankaartia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis id="B909EAF77918FFB943429E5ED5C8F9A2" box="[531,746,1537,1561]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="280">Blankaartia gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is probably identical with 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667918FFB945599E5DD21BF9A2" authority="(Tragardh, 1905)" baseAuthorityName="Tragardh" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[1032,1337,1537,1561]" class="Arachnida" family="Trombiculidae" genus="Blankaartia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ardeae">
<emphasis id="B909EAF77918FFB945599E5DD34DF9A2" box="[1032,1135,1537,1561]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="280">B. ardeae</emphasis>
(Trägårdh, 1905)
</taxonomicName>
described from 
<subSubSection id="C367656E7918FFB940BA9E7CD362F97E" pageId="16" pageNumber="280" type="description">
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667918FFB940BA9E7CD5A2F980" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[491,640,1571,1595]" class="Aves" family="Ardeidae" genus="Ardea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pelecaniformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="280" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cinerea">
<emphasis id="B909EAF77918FFB940BA9E7CD5A2F980" box="[491,640,1571,1595]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="280">Ardea cinerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667918FFB943F99E7CD470F980" box="[680,850,1571,1595]" class="Aves" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pelecaniformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="280" phylum="Chordata" rank="order">Pelecaniformes</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D667918FFB9420F9E7CD4F5F980" box="[862,983,1571,1595]" class="Aves" family="Ardeidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pelecaniformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="280" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Ardeidae</taxonomicName>
) in 
<collectingCountry id="F36A76757918FFB942AE9E7CD36FF980" box="[1023,1101,1571,1595]" name="Sudan" pageId="16" pageNumber="280">Sudan</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49B9F8077918FFB9450B9E7CD3F5F980" box="[1114,1239,1571,1595]" country="Sudan" name="An Nil al Abyad" pageId="16" pageNumber="280">White Nile</collectingRegion>
), as one can conclude on the base of its redescription made by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B147918FFB942279E19D318F9E5" author="Oudemans A. C." box="[886,1082,1606,1630]" pageId="16" pageNumber="280" pagination="1 - 230" refId="ref11919" refString="Oudemans A. C. 1912. Die bis jetzt bekannten Larven von Thrombidiidae und Erythraeidae. Zoologische Jahrbucher suppl., 14: 1 - 230." type="journal article" year="1912">Oudemans (1912)</bibRefCitation>
. However, this redescription is somewhat incomplete (metric data include only length and width of idiosoma and scutum, and lengths of legs). Comparison of 
<typeStatus id="54C688477918FFB943AA9ED4D40BF918" box="[763,809,1675,1699]" pageId="16" pageNumber="280">type</typeStatus>
specimens is urgently needed, but places of 
<typeStatus id="54C688477918FFB9447A9ED4D27BF918" box="[1323,1369,1675,1699]" pageId="16" pageNumber="280">type</typeStatus>
deposition are currently unknown for both species (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC4B147918FFB9422B9EF2D317F97E" author="Stekolnikov A. A." box="[890,1077,1709,1733]" pageId="16" pageNumber="280" pagination="1 - 233" refId="ref11947" refString="Stekolnikov A. A. 2018. Taxonomy and distribution of African chiggers (Acariformes, Trombiculidae). European Journal of Taxonomy, 395: 1 - 233. doi: 10.5852 / ejt. 2018.395" type="journal article" year="2018">Stekolnikov 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</subSubSection>
</paragraph>
